    <h2>TERMS AND CONDITION</h2>
    <p>The below-mentioned segments are eligible to apply for a Rahtriya Mahila Bank Loan:</p>
    <p> . Sole Proprietors</p>
    <p> . Partnership Firms</p> 
    <p> . Co-operative Societies</p>
    <p> . Public and Private Limited Companies</p>
    <p> Applicants with work experience of minimum 2 years; business continuity of minimum 2 years is required for the self-employed.</p>
    <p>The applicant should be at least 21 years of age at loan application and should not be over 60 years at loan maturity.</p>
    <p> The minimum take-home income should be  Rs. 25000/- per month.</p>
    <p> Co-applicant (Spouse/Parents/Children) are allowed in case of HL and LAP.</p>

    <h3>Documents Requirements - Rashtriya Mahila Bank business loans</h3>
    <p> The following documents need to be furnished while applying for business loans in RMB.</p>
    <h3>Income Documents</h3>
    <p>Documents for Salaried:</p>
    <h3>Identity Proof:</h3> <p> Any one from  Driving License, PAN Card, Voter ID Card, Aadhar Card, Proprietor ID card, ID card of a partner of Director (in case of a company), etc.</p>
    <h3>Address Proof:</h3> <p>Any one from valid Passport, Aadhar Card, Property tax bill, Utility bill, etc.</p>
    <p>Last 3 months? salary slip</p>
    <p>Passport size photographs (2)</p>
    <p>Last 6 months? Bank statement of the salary account</p>
    <p>Latest Form 16.</p>
    <h3>Documents for Self-employed:</h3>
    <h3>Identity Proof:</h3> <p> Any one from Driving License, PAN Card, Voter ID Card, Aadhar Card, Proprietor ID card, ID card of a partner of Director (in case of a company), etc.</p>
    <h3>Address Proof:</h3> <p> Any one from valid Passport, Aadhar Card, Property tax bill, Utility bill, etc.</p>
    <p>ITR for the last 2 years</p>
    <p>Financial Documents (Balance Sheet, P & L account, Tax Audit report  and Schedules to Balance Sheet) & primary current account statement of the company for the last 6 months</p>
    <p>Statement of current obligations of the applicant, i.e. the other EMIs being paid currently paying, the credit cards along with limits and so on.</p>
    <h3>Proof of Business Continuity/employment</h3>
    F<h3>or Salaried:</h3> <p> Appointment letter or Form 16 from 2 years or earlier</p>
    <h3>For Self-employed:</h3> <p> Sales/Service Tax registration certificate or Income Tax Returns from 2 years or earlier</p>
    <h3>Property Documents (For LAP/HL)</h3>
    <h3>For property under construction ?</h3> <p> Proof of booking amount paid, Allotment letter and Payment schedule</p>
    <h3>Ready-to-use Property ?</h3> <p>Parent Documents, Sale Deed, latest Property tax paid receipt, Latest EC  and Khatha  or 7/11 extract</p>
    <h3>Plot and Self-construction ?</h3> <p> Parent Documents, Sale Deed, Latest EC  and Khatha  or 7/11 extract</p>
    <h3>Interest Rate -</h3> <p>Rashtriya Mahila bank business loans</p>
    <p>The Rashtriya Mahila Bank Business Loan interest rate varies in the range of 10.15% to 13.65% per annum.</p>
    <h3>The maximum business loan amount provided by Rashtriya Mahila Bank differs for various categories of applicants as follows</h3>
    <p>For service enterprises and retail traders: Maximum of Rs. 5,00,00,000</p>
    <p>For manufacturing enterprises: Maximum of Rs. 20,00,00,000</p>
    <p>Collateral free loan: Up to Rs. 1,00,00,000 (under CGTMSE cover of Govt. of India)</p>


